1
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:06,000
1st: Get hooked

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,033
I started pouring a ton of time into research.

3
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:10,367
Ugh… I still don’t get it!

4
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:12,700
Oh! That kid with the bell earlier…

5
00:00:13,100 --> 00:00:15,100
Wait—could it be those people, maybe?

6
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:15,767
Right?

7
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:17,667
They’re human!

8
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:19,600
That’s complicated!

9
00:00:20,133 --> 00:00:25,200
So all the skeleton enemies used to be human?

10
00:00:25,533 --> 00:00:27,733
Yeah… that’s complicated.

11
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:29,667
I ended up taking them out…

12
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:32,300
And I couldn’t turn them back.

13
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:35,467
And, uh… I’m kinda curious about what’s going on behind the scenes, too.

14
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:37,333
So, with that said—

15
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:40,533
Like, by watching the sto—story again…

16
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:42,167
You can really—uh—more…

17
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:44,400
Like, get pulled deeper into the story…

18
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:46,733
And get even more hooked, you know!

19
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:50,767
2nd: I’m a sucker for it

20
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,567
Hey—look, look, look, look!

21
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,600
Yeah, yeah, yeah—so like, what Marvel stuff do you recommend?

22
00:00:50,767 --> 00:00:52,400
Like, your top picks.

23
00:00:52,533 --> 00:00:54,533
If you’ve got more, tell me—seriously.

24
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:55,700
I kinda wanna watch something.

25
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:57,600
Recommendations, huh…

26
00:00:57,767 --> 00:00:59,700
But at this point, I mean—

27
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:02,567
Isn’t Doctor Strange the move? (laughs)

28
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:04,433
True—Doctor Strange is…

29
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:05,333
It does look fun.

30
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:07,733
Doctor Strange is, like—

31
00:01:07,733 --> 00:01:10,067
It’s got that whole magic vibe.

32
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:12,367
Yeah—not just regular action,

33
00:01:12,367 --> 00:01:14,333
It’s got magic stuff too, so…

34
00:01:14,667 --> 00:01:16,533
I think it’ll really click with people who are into that.

35
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:18,433
Me? I love fantasy and magic—

36
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:19,700
Like, a LOT.

37
00:01:20,167 --> 00:01:20,633
Seriously?!

38
00:01:20,633 --> 00:01:21,100
Yeah.

39
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:22,700
Then I think Doctor Strange is totally your thing.

40
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:25,133
Oh—then maybe I’ll start with that one.

41
00:01:25,133 --> 00:01:26,200
If so.

42
00:01:26,267 --> 00:01:27,600
No way! Watch it, watch it, watch it!

43
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:28,667
I will, I will!

44
00:01:28,667 --> 00:01:29,700
Yesss! I’m so happy—we’ve got more to talk about now!

45
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:30,733
I’m so happy!

46
00:01:30,733 --> 00:01:36,233
I’m such a sucker for magic—when someone says “magic,” I’m like, “Ooh, that’s so fantasy!” (laughs)

47
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,267
3rd: Stick your nose in

48
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,400
I’m thinking about buying a gun.

49
00:01:38,533 --> 00:01:39,333
Huh?!

50
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:41,333
Can just anyone buy one?

51
00:01:41,467 --> 00:01:42,500
Yeah—sit next to him.

52
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:44,467
And order a whiskey-and-water.

53
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:45,667
Apparently that’s the signal.

54
00:01:46,033 --> 00:01:46,600
Oh!

55
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,433
Oh, really…

56
00:01:48,767 --> 00:01:50,067
Come to think of it, that guy earlier—

57
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:51,733
He ordered a whiskey-and-water too.

58
00:01:52,267 --> 00:01:53,600
I wasn’t totally convinced, but—

59
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,233
What I saw just now sealed it.

60
00:01:55,367 --> 00:01:57,633
I’ll come back another day and give it a shot.

61
00:01:58,167 --> 00:02:02,333
A straight-laced guy like you sticks his nose into the underworld, you’re gonna get burned.

62
00:02:02,567 --> 00:02:06,367
4th: Read the room

63
00:02:02,567 --> 00:02:05,600
There are still some really worried Yukimin out there, but—

64
00:02:06,067 --> 00:02:07,167
Like, kinda…

65
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,033
Really, like…

66
00:02:09,367 --> 00:02:11,667
How do I put it—no matter what I do,

67
00:02:12,133 --> 00:02:13,433
“Are you okay? Are you okay?”

68
00:02:13,767 --> 00:02:15,100
“You okay?” like that.

69
00:02:15,433 --> 00:02:16,567
That kind of, like—

70
00:02:16,567 --> 00:02:20,700
There used to be a lot of super worrywart Yukimin.

71
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:22,167
And stuff!

72
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:23,633
What else was there…

73
00:02:24,167 --> 00:02:27,167
Like, for every little thing Lamy said or did,

74
00:02:27,433 --> 00:02:29,667
They’d be like, “Is that okay? Is that really okay?”

75
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:32,433
There were a lot of Yukimin with that vibe.

76
00:02:32,767 --> 00:02:34,667
But now it’s like—

77
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,200
Yukimin these days, you know—

78
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:40,333
They’re pretty good at reading the room!

79
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:44,367
Final: Get ahead of it

80
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:43,733
But man, there aren’t many that seem useful.

81
00:02:44,367 --> 00:02:46,100
For now, I’m going with 3!

82
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:52,167
Oh—ugh, I hate this.

83
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:53,500
What, what, what?!

84
00:02:53,533 --> 00:02:54,700
I can’t move!

85
00:02:55,433 --> 00:02:56,400
Heeey! (cute)

86
00:02:56,767 --> 00:02:59,333
What am I supposed to do?!

87
00:03:02,467 --> 00:03:03,200
Like this?!

88
00:03:03,533 --> 00:03:07,300
Get ahead of it, get ahead of it!

